{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7e246363-aa8c-4741-9241-29988d190f4a","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, you need to make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n**Key behavioral differences to expect:**\n\n- Run tests with `dotnet test` as usual, but the runner is now Microsoft.Testing.Platform under the hood.\n- `.runsettings` files still work, but some VSTest-specific settings may not apply.\n- Command-line syntax differs slightly (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` via the bridge or `--treenode-filter` natively).\n- If you use `dotnet test`, a compatibility layer maps most options automatically.\n\n**If you hit issues**, you may also want to add an explicit entry point (though MSTest.Sdk usually handles this):\n```xml\n<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92818e9f-4a89-47bd-8613-4b6c1a958de0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request for a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":397},"id":"c0da7498-b901-4e13-a70b-2b2de222e4f4","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:04:39.011Z","parentId":"47b12ea7-955c-478a-a064-d1c5e756925f"}
